  <bioghist id="aspace_230adcb2f9c0f7302b87cd87b3b6e0fb">
    <head>Biographical Note</head>
<p>George Carter is an activist and writer who researches HIV and AIDS treatment and prevention, with a focus on alternative treatments. Carter joined ACT UP/New York in 1989 and as part of the Treatment and Data Committee, and wrote and distributed extensive charts detailing the latest drugs and information available to fight AIDS and related opportunistic infections. These tables included information on pharmaceutical drugs as well as alternative and complementary treatments.</p><p>Carter was the director for the Treatment Information Development for DAAIR (Direct Access Alternative Information Resources), a not-for-profit buyers' club for alternative treatments. He also started the Foundation for Integrative AIDS Research (FIAR) in conjunction with Columbia University to pursue clinical studies where drug treatment is not readily available.</p>  </bioghist>
